title: For Sale/Trade:  Quality holsters for Glock, LCR, J-frame .38 and Taurus
postcontent: Inside the Waist Band holsters, one for Taurus and LCR, or one for a Glock - you bought your new carry gun, now you need to carry it.  Why pay brand new prices when you can get the same thing at a significant discount?  Now you have some quality gear to choose from.  Both of these holsters come from highly-reputable American companies that offer lifetime warranties on their products.  The Tucker Gun Leather holster fits the LCR and small-framed taurus revolvers.  The LCR is a popular carry gun and this holster fits any of the snubby .38, .22LR, .22Mag, .357, or LCRX style revolvers.  It also fits small-framed (.38 Special or 8-round .22) Taurus snubbie revolvers and S&W J-frame revolvers.  I had taken it for granted that since the holster came with an LCR, it was for an LCR only.  I was asked if it will fit all the other revolvers, so I tried them and they do fit.  It is high-quality leather "rough side out," with a lifetime warranty, and retails for $83 on the Tucker Gun Leather website as the "cover up" IWB style.  This holster has a pretty ingenious variable-depth retaining-bracket.  A small allen wrench is used to choose one of 5 optional depths to position the holster.  Choose anywhere within the two inch range that suits you - not many holsters allow you to do that.  I would imagine it especially handy for frequent belt changes or grip-angle changes.   Rough side out makes the smooth side lay against the firearm (protecting the finish), and the rough side facilitates better airflow and traction where it is needed.  It hasn't even been used enough to break it in.  I will take $63 for it, by itself.  Foxx holsters are top notch gun leather with a lifetime warranty and go for $39 all day long on Amazon.  This particular model will (perfectly) fit all of the smaller framed (9mm/.40 cal./.357 Sig) Glock pistols.  I don't believe it will fit any other model of pistol that doesn't closely approximate the same dimensions of a small-framed Glock pistol.  Foxx holsters are a hybrid (leather/kydex) IWB - combining the strength/rigidity of kydex where it is needed and comfort of leather where it will be appreciated, all in a light weight package.  Hybrid holsters originally sold for over a hundred dollars each a few years back, when there was no competition, but have recently come down to the fifty - seventy dollar range.  They are a simple design to build and nearly all of them work great - Foxx holsters are comfortably among that higher-quality group.  Foxx holsters use .8mm Kydex instead of the industry standard of .6mm, and they have fewer returned/broken holsters than the other companies making hybrid leather/kydex holsters.  I will take $29 for this fine piece of equipment.  Both of these holsters look and feel nearly new - if I was right-handed, this listing would never have been posted.  A recent trade landed me these holsters - the firearms were both in nearly-new condition and so were their holsters.  *****************************************************************I am interested in a traditional AR15A2 full-length buttstock, the dreaded "three-position" buffer tube, a traditional USGI sling for an AR-15, or a Hearltand brand magazine extension for a Mosin.  I will trade the Tucker for the buttstock, and the Foxx holster for the Heartland magazine extension. Also interested in those useless plastic stripper clips that come with GECO ammunition.
